<DATELINE>PARIS (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Petite Soeur Magdeleine de Jesus, author and
founder of an order of Roman Catholic nuns, died Monday. She was 91.
   Born Magdeleine Hutin, she founded the Fraternite des Petites
Soeurs de Jesus (the Little Sisters of Jesus) in 1939, in the
