<HEAD>Three East Germans Hire a Cab to the West</HEAD>
<HEAD>With AM-East Germany, Bjt</HEAD>
<DATELINE>HAMBURG, West Germany (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Three East Germans had a little
trouble convincing a taxi driver he could actually drive them
across the border to Hamburg, but he agreed to do it anyway.
   Late Thursday night, Hamburg police noticed a taxi with East
German license plates cruising through the city, officials said
Friday.
   ``The driver apparently didn't know his way around the city very
well, so police offered their assistance,'' said a Hamburg police
spokesman, who did not give his name.
   ``The passengers laughed and said they just visited'' an aunt in
Hamburg, the spokesman said. ``The only difficulty they had was
persuading the taxi driver that such a visit was suddenly possible
without any difficulties.''
   East Germany's Communist authorities on Thursday threw open the
borders with West Germany.
