<SECOND>AM-BRF--Night Stalker,0160</SECOND>
<HEAD>Jailhouse Privileges for Richard Ramirez are Temporarily Suspended</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Convicted ``Night Stalker'' Richard Ramirez
had his jailhouse television and visiting privileges suspended for
10 days after he vandalized a ceiling air vent, authorities said
Friday.
   Ramirez was disciplined for damaging the vent while taking a
shower at the Men's Central Jail on Thursday, said Sheriff's deputy
George Ducoulombier.
   Ramirez was sentenced to death Tuesday and was awaiting transfer
to San Quentin.
   The incident was being ``handled strictly as a disciplinary
action,'' the deputy said. ``It is not considered by the custody
authorities as an attempt to escape. ... The air vent was not large
enough for a person to get into.''
   Ramirez faces the gas chamber for his conviction of 13 murders
and 30 charges stemming from a string of nighttime rapes and
burglaries. As with all death sentences, Ramirez's case will
automatically be appealed to state Supreme Court.
</TEXT>
