<HEAD>Eds: Members who used a0872, AM-Recess Appointments, transmitted
Thursday under a Washington dateline, are asked to use the following story:</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Associated Press erroneously reported on
Thursday, in a story about backlogged presidential appointments,
that Vaughn R. Walker's nomination to be a federal judge in
California was snarled in a nepotism controversy.
   It is the nomination of John M. Walker _ President Bush's cousin
_ which has been the subject of such controversy. John Walker,
currently a U.S. district judge in New York, has been nominated to
be a federal appeals court judge.
