<FIRST>r i AM-Czechoslovak-Train     11-10 0156</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Czechoslovak-Train,0161</SECOND>
<HEAD>5 Killed When Express Train Rams Idled Passenger Train</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PRAGUE, Czechoslovakia (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An express train rammed into an
idled passenger train Friday, killing five people and injuring 52,
the official CTK news agency reported.
   The northbound Baltorient Express was en route from Prague to
East Germany when the two trains crashed near Nove Kopisty, about
45 miles north of Prague, CTK said. The impact destroyed four rail
cars and derailed six cars of the express train, CTK said.
   One of the five dead was an East German, the news agency said.
It did not give the nationalieties of any of the other dead or
injured.
   Thirty people were hospitalized with injuries and 22 others were
treated and released, CTK said.
   The news agency did not say how many people were aboard the two
trains.
   CTK said soldiers were helping railway workers clear the
wreckage. Traffic was rerouted throughout the day, it said.
</TEXT>
