<HEAD>Automotive Industries Names Acura Legend Top Car</HEAD>
<DATELINE>RADNOR, Pa. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Automotive Industries magazine Friday called
the Acura Legend the ideal car and said Japanese cars still
outperform their American competition.
   The magazine compared price, performance, quality, safety and
resale value of 22 American and foreign cars.
   Acura Legend won top honors, followed by the Toyota Camry IL-4,
the Honda Accord DX, the Buick Electra and the Oldsmobile 88.
