<DATELINE>DALLAS (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A Dallas police officer riding in Philippine
President Corazon Aquino's motorcade was injured Friday when a
driver ran into his motorcycle, police said.
   The officer, whose identity was not released, was taken to
Baylor Medical Center for treatment, according to Michael McMurray,
a communications officer for the Dallas Police Department.
   ``We don't believe it was serious,'' McMurray said. ``We think
he's in good shape.''
   An initial report that the accident occurred during a motorcade
for President Bush, who was also visiting the city, was false,
McMurray said.
   The 6:13 p.m. accident did not delay the motorcade, which was
taking Mrs. Aquino to a hotel for a private dinner. Her Dallas stop
was the last of a seven-city tour the president is making to to
promote foreign investment in the Philippines.
   A woman driving a BMW apparently did not see the intersection
was blocked off and hit the motorcycle, said Cpl. J.W. Lawton, who
investigated the accident.
   The driver was cited for a routine violation and no alcohol was
involved, he said.
