<HEAD>USG Announces Election of New CEO</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CHICAGO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   USG Corp.'s board of directors have elected
Eugene Connolly president and chief executive officer.
   Connolly, 57, currently is an executive vice president.
   Anthony Falvo, 59, an executive vice president, was elected
chief operating officer of USG Corp., the company announced
Thursday.
   USG is a major manufacturer of building products, and is the
parent company of United States Gypsum Co., USG Interiors Inc., and
L&amp;W Supply Corp.
   The two executives assume their new duties Jan. 1, 1990.
   Connolly replaces Robert Day, who plans to retire in May 1990,
and Falvo replaces Ralph Jones, who will serve as an advisor until
his retirement that month.
   ``We are fortunate to have two outstanding leaders in Gene
Connolly and Tony Falvo to assume the role and responsibilities of
running USG Corp.,'' Day said in a statement.
   ``Each has more than 30 years experience in our corporation
including key aspects of our building products business and a
proven track record with customers, employees and the financial
community,'' Day said.
