<FILEID>AP-NR-11-10-89 0804EST</FILEID>
<FIRST>r f BC-HungarianPlayboy     11-10 0175</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Hungarian Playboy,0182</SECOND>
<HEAD>Playboy Magazine Plans Hungarian Edition</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CHICAGO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A Hungarian edition of Playboy magazine will hit
the newsstands in the East European country at the end of this
month, Playboy Enterprises Inc. announced.
   ``Playboy will satisfy the strong demand for an upscale
international men's entertainment magazine,'' William Stokkan,
president of Playboy's Licensing and Merchandising Group, said in a
statement issued Thursday.
   The magazine will be marketed and distributed by Hungarian
publisher VIPress, Chicago-based Playboy said.
   The first edition, scheduled to go on sale Nov. 29, will carry
over December's contents of the American edition, including an
interview with Soviet world chess champion Garry Kasparov and the
first of a four-part series on the history of the magazine.
   But the Hungarian edition also will include works by Hungarian
writers Ivan Mandy and Istvan Eorsi, an article on the far-reaching
consequences of Karl Marx and a column by Andras Toro on credit
cards and investments, Playboy said.
   The publisher of the Hungarian edition is Dezso Futasz, formerly
with the daily newspaper Magyar Nemzet.
</TEXT>
