<FIRST>r f AM-MortgageRates     11-10 0105</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Mortgage Rates,0109</SECOND>
<HEAD>Mortgage Rates Slip</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Fixed-rate home mortgages dipped to 9.79
percent this week, their lowest level in three months, according to
a national survey released Friday by the Federal Home Loan Mortgage
Corp.
   That was down from a 9.82 percent rate last week and represented
the lowest level since fixed-rate mortgages averaged 9.68 percent
for the week ended Aug. 4.
   On one-year adjustable rate mortgages, lenders were asking an
average initial rate of 8.52 percent this week, down from 8.55
percent the week before and the lowest level for adjustable rate
mortgages since the last week of December, 1988.
</TEXT>
