<FIRST>u f AM-TreasuryAuction     11-10 0103</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Treasury Auction,0107</SECOND>
<HEAD>Treasury Sells $10 Billion in 36-Day Bills</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Treasury Department auctioned off $10
billion in short-term debt on Friday as it continued replenishing
the government's depleted coffers following the increase in the
debt limit.
   Friday's auction consisted of the sale of 36-day cash management
bills, which carried a discount interest rate of 8.14 percent and
an equivalent coupon interest rate of 8.32 percent with each
$10,000 in face value selling for $9,918.60.
   It was the third auction since the government debt limit was
raised to $3.1 trillion Wednesday, narrowly averting the first U.S.
default in history.
</TEXT>
