agreement by NBC Sports on a four-year, $600 million contract to
televise National Basketball Association games starting next season.
   Gainers among the blue chips included International Business
Machines, up } at 98[; McDonald's, up ] at 31\; American Telephone
&amp; Telegraph, up { at 44[, and Philip Morris, up \ at 41~.
   Volume on the floor of the Big Board came to 131.80 million
shares, down from 143.39 million in the previous session.
Nationwide, consolidated volume in NYSE-listed issues, including
trades in those stocks on regional exchanges and in the
over-the-counter market, totaled 157.33 million shares.
   As measured by Wilshire Associates' index of more than 5,000
actively traded stocks, the market increased $19.69 billion, or
0.60 percent, in value.
   The NYSE's composite index of all its listed common stocks added
1.14 to 187.89.
   Standard &amp; Poor's industrial index rose 3.23 to 386.45, and
S&amp;P's 500-stock composite index was up 2.53 at 339.10.
   The NASDAQ composite index for the over-the-counter market
gained 2.12 to 455.79. At the American Stock Exchange, the market
value index closed at 371.47, up 1.06.
