<DATELINE>CHICAGO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An inventor who has spent more than a decade
proving toys aren't all fun and games has scored a patent victory
over Mattel Inc. over the track for its popular ``Hot Wheels''
model vehicles.
   A federal court jury on Thursday awarded Jerome Lemelson $24.8
million in damages after finding earlier in the week that Mattel
willfully infringed on Lemelson's patent, a flexible track on which
the tiny metal Hot Wheels' cars run. ``I am floating on cloud
nine,'' Lemelson said Friday.
</TEXT>
<DATELINE>MINNEAPOLIS (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Already reeling from a worldwide glut of
furs, Minnesota's mink ranchers have had their hackles raised by
animal rights protesters intent on spoiling the product's image.
   The state's 140 ranchers expect a drop in revenue from this
year's pelting because auction houses in New York and Seattle are
forecasting a third consecutive year of lower prices.
   Minnesota is the third-leading U.S. producer of mink, behind No.
1 Wisconsin and Utah.
</TEXT>
