week Friday with a rally that featured a few issues benefiting from
the political news in Germany. The Dow Jones average of 30
industrials climbed 21.92 to 2,625.61.
   Bond prices finished little changed.
   The dollar rose, especially against the West German mark.
   Grain and soybean futures surged; precious metals, copper and
energy futures declined; sugar futures rose and livestock and pork
futures were mixed.
